Azure Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) manages who can perform actions on Azure resources.

Core components:

* Security principal (user/app/group)
* Role definition
* Scope

Examples of roles:

* Owner
* Contributor
* Reader

For example, a finance manager may only view billing data while engineers deploy resources.

A real-life use case is enforcing least privilege.

Another example is separating Dev, Test, and Production permissions.

RBAC ensures secure and organized resource governance.
